var.info:
last point of the given box;
( 0 stands for the last point in the FFT grid )

BEWARE: irmax is a 2D array of the form: irmax(3,n_proj_boxes)

subsection.text:
Order of m-components for each l in the output:
1, cos(phi), sin(phi), cos(2*phi), sin(2*phi), .., cos(l*phi), sin(l*phi)
where phi is the polar angle:x=r cos(theta)cos(phi), y=r cos(theta)sin(phi) This is determined in file Modules/ylmr2.f90 that calculates spherical harmonics.
for l=1: 1 pz (m=0) 2 px (real combination of m=+/-1 with cosine) 3 py (real combination of m=+/-1 with sine)
for l=2: 1 dz2 (m=0) 2 dzx (real combination of m=+/-1 with cosine) 3 dzy (real combination of m=+/-1 with sine) 4 dx2-y2 (real combination of m=+/-2 with cosine) 5 dxy (real combination of m=+/-2 with sine)
